{{Infobox Academic Conference | title = International Conference on Business Information Systems | history = 1997– | abbreviation = BIS | discipline = [[information system]]s | publisher = [[Springer Science+Business Media|Springer]] | frequency = annual | website = [http://bisconf.info BISconf.info] }}
[[File:BIS Conference.png|thumb|upright=1|<center>BIS conference logo</center>]]
'''BIS conference''' (International Conference on Business Information Systems) - is an annual [[Academic conference|conference]] organized by the Department of Information Systems, [[Poznań University of Economics]].
[[File:BIS 2013.jpg|thumb|upright=1|<center>16th BIS Conference (2013)</center>]]
First BIS conference was organized in 1997 in [[Poznań]].<ref>[http://archive.kie.ue.poznan.pl/1st_bis/1st_bis.htm 1st International Conference on Business Information Systems], BIS 1997</ref> The BIS conference is a well-respected event joining international researchers and practitioners to discuss the wide range of the development, implementation, application and improvement of [[Business software|business applications]] and systems. General Chair of the conference is Prof. Witold Abramowicz.
