{{Orphan|date=March 2017}}

The '''Lobster College''' is a four-day-long educational program held in [[Prospect Harbor, Maine]]. The college has been held every year since 2001.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://archive.bangordailynews.com/2001/03/26/college-offers-ins-outs-of-lobster-cuisine-trade/ | title=College offers ins, outs of lobster cuisine, trade | publisher=Bangor Daily News | date=March 26, 2001 | accessdate=January 10, 2014 | author=Young, Susan | pages=B1}}</ref> It was founded by Dr. [[Robert Bayer]] via the [[Lobster Institute]], and a local innkeeper, to help educate [[tourist]]s and the general public about [[lobster]]s, [[lobster fishing|lobstering]], and the effects of the lobster industry on the state economy. Lecturers include academics, lobster fishermen, and others involved in the [[seafood industry]] such as restaurant owners.<ref name="chicago">{{cite web | url=http://articles#chicagotribune#com/2008-08-19/news/0808180679_1_lobster-institute-robert-bayer-american-lobster | title=Lobster is meaty subject | publisher=Chicago Tribune | date=August 19, 2008 | accessdate=January 10, 2014 | author=George, Jason}}</ref>

